          <Comment>This sequence change creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu280*) in the BLM gene. It is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. This variant is not present in population databases (ExAC no frequency). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with BLM-related disease. Loss-of-function variants in BLM are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 17407155). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
