          <GermlineClassification>Pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment>The c.839_888del50 pathogenic mutation, located in coding exon 3 of the BLM gene, results from a deletion of 50 nucleotides at nucleotide positions 839 to 888, causing a translational frameshift with a predicted alternate stop codon (p.L280*). This variant is considered to be rare based on population cohorts in the Genome Aggregation Database (gnomAD). This alteration is expected to result in loss of function by premature protein truncation or nonsense-mediated mRNA decay. As such, this alteration is interpreted as a disease-causing mutation.</Comment>
